TASK05: Cybercrime Awareness Case Study & Prevention Guide 

Part A – Case Study: Cyberbullying 

Tool Used: I used Google for research and Google Docs to write and format the case study. 

What I Studied: 
Cyberbullying refers to the use of digital platforms, social media, messaging apps, or online forums to harass, threaten, or humiliate others. For this case study, I examined a common scenario faced by college students in India: a student receiving repeated mocking comments and morphed images shared across a WhatsApp class group, leading to emotional distress and academic decline.
The case highlighted how cyberbullying differs from traditional bullying: it follows the victim everywhere, operates 24/7, and can reach a large audience instantly. 

What Surprised Me Most / One Habit I Will Change: 
What surprised me most while researching this topic was that a large number of cyberbullying victims never report the incident either out of shame or because they believe no action will be taken. I also did not realise how severely it impacts mental health, sometimes leading to anxiety, depression, and academic dropout. 



Part B – Prevention Checklist: Stay Safe Online 

Tool Used: I used Google Docs and Canva to create the checklist. 

What I Built: 
A practical "Stay Safe Online" checklist with 12 specific, actionable tips for college students in India. 

One Thing I Found Difficult / Interesting:
The most interesting part of this task was discovering that India has a dedicated Cyber Crime Portal where students can report online harassment anonymously. The difficult part was selecting only  12 tips from a very long list. Almost every point felt essential and important to include for student safety. 






